b'In summary, if we assume even a small portion of marketing and r&d spend is being incorrectly categorized as an expense rather than investment, then $PSTG looks cheap on a EV/operating profit basis. 9/10'
b'Of course, as investors, we would rather see $PSTG plow all the money they can into r&d and marketing if they can continue to achieve the ROIC they have been in this growing market. 8/10'

b'If we assume that $PSTG can grow gross profit through 2022 at 25% using the same levels of marketing/r&d spend as 2020, than we arrive at a gross profit of 1.8B and an operating profit of 446M. This would imply a 2022 EV/operating profit multiple of 13.4. 7/10'

b'$PSTG currently has an EV of just under $6B. In TTM they report 1.7B or revenue which becomes 1.2B of gross profit. The company has invested almost the entirety of its gross profit every year in sales and r&d. This leads to a persistently near zero net income. 4/10 https://t.co/GptxJK5Url'
b'$PSTG reports a net promoter score of 82 for their products! This is basically unheard of in any industry. 3/10'

b'$PSTG is a provider of all-flash memory both as a service via AWS/Azure and "on-premise". I am not an expert in the business model, but long-story short all-flash memory is taking over from legacy storage solutions as the technology improves (i.e. the industry is growing). 2/10'
